The grammar seems to allow annotations, but are we handling them?
https://github.com/ballerina-platform/ballerina-lang/pull/21209/files#diff-0e72b59e6b830c29e9c6161f3bb4177aR844
The following should fail since an annotation allowed only on const is being used with a let var, but doesn't.
int globalVar = 5;

const annotation v1 on source const;

public function main() {
    int b = let @v1 int x = 4 in 2 * x * globalVar;
}

